Sentencas: Sr-vacancy compensated Nb-doped SrTiO3 with the nominal composition Sr0.94Ti0.9Nb0.1O3 has been evaluated as a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) anode material in terms of redox stability and electrochemical properties.
Titulo: Electrochemical characterization and redox behavior of Nb-doped SrTiO3

Sentencas: Sr0.94Ti0.9Nb0.1O3 has been synthesized with a recently developed modified glycine-nitrate process.
Titulo: Electrochemical characterization and redox behavior of Nb-doped SrTiO3

Sentencas: The phase purity and redox behavior have been analyzed with XRD and TGA.
Titulo: Electrochemical characterization and redox behavior of Nb-doped SrTiO3

Sentencas: The electrochemical properties of Sr0.94Ti0.9Nb0.1O3 and a composite electrode of Sr0.94Ti0.9Nb0.1O3/YSZ have been investigated by electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) on cone shaped electrodes and on electrodes in a symmetrical cell configuration.
Titulo: Electrochemical characterization and redox behavior of Nb-doped SrTiO3

Sentencas: The experiments indicated that the Nb-doped SrTiO3 electrodes were redox stable and showed a potential ability to be used as a part of a SOFC anode.
Titulo: Electrochemical characterization and redox behavior of Nb-doped SrTiO3

Sentencas: The electrochemical activity appeared to be governed by the concentration of defect species (especially Ti3+ and V-0(++)) in the vicinity of the triple phase boundaries.
Titulo: Electrochemical characterization and redox behavior of Nb-doped SrTiO3

Sentencas: However, the electrocatalytic activity of the materials was not sufficient and it needs to be improved if Nb-doped SrTiO3 based materials are to be realized as SOFC anodes.
Titulo: Electrochemical characterization and redox behavior of Nb-doped SrTiO3
